column1: No details to locate the garden gauge exactly, but elevation, distance to walls, and being closer to the church to SW means it could have been around here

1869 Note says “I can't help but thinking that the fact of NO rain being registered in July and but little in June while for the 2 months 1.75 is reported from Ridgeway by Miss Phillips may be attributed partly to evaporation, still the amount must have been small”
1969 July Aug bracketed with value 1.37, but note above says there was no rain in July registered, so 1.37 should be for August
1885 Gauge moved a few feet and raised (seemingly from 1ft to 4ft above ground)
1897 Dec amount computed. The 2 records not very accordant
